#Made By Neal Aringale

Overview
This repository contains the code for a To-Do app/website created using HTML. The app allows users to manage their tasks, set priorities, and add due dates for effective task management.

Features
Task Management: Add, delete, and mark tasks as completed.
Priority Settings: Set task priority (high, medium, low) during creation.
Due Dates: Add due dates to tasks for better organization.
Simple and Responsive Design: User-friendly interface for seamless task management.
Getting Started
Follow the steps below to get the To-Do app/website up and running:

Prerequisites
Web browser
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/todo-app.git
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd todo-app
Open index.html in your web browser.

Usage
Add a Task:

Type the task in the input field.
Click the "Add" button.
Delete a Task:

Click the "Delete" button next to the task.
Mark as Completed:

Check the checkbox next to the task.
Set Priority:

Choose priority from the dropdown during task creation.
Set Due Date:

Select a due date from the calendar during task creation.
Customization
Feel free to customize the app to meet your specific requirements. You can modify the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files as needed.

